<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../static/css/styles.css">
    <title>Sub Particles</title>
</head>
<body>
    {{#particles}}
        <div
            data-is-particle="true"
            data-fb-key="{{key}}"
            data-access-key="{{access_key}}"
            data-claimed="{{claimed}}"
            data-nickname="{{nickname}}"
            class="noshow"
        ></div>
    {{/particles}}

    <a href="/" class="nav">home</a>
    <h1>Sub Particles</h1>
    <p>is a way to create a virtual community for a YouTube channel's fanbase. Every channel's particle system is populated with the same number of particles as channel subscribers. Particles can be claimed by fans and given a custom name. If there are no unclaimed particles in the system then a new one can be spawned by subscribing to the YouTube channel. Created by <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@ranchgod3752" class="link" target="_blank">Reese</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@charlieuu" class="link" target="_blank">Charlie</a>.
    </p>
    <h2>Systems:</h2>
    <div class="grid">
        <a href="/particles/reese" onclick="changeDB('reese')" class="button">Reese's Particles</a>
        <a href="/particles/charlie" onclick="changeDB('charlie')" class="button">Charlie's Particles</a>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/p5.js/1.5.0/p5.min.js"></script>
    <script src="../static/javascript/PostClaimParticle.js"></script>
    <script src="../static/javascript/MainCanvas.js"></script>
</body>
</html>